From b5f563ef3ad8195330d1f5b519f5948662112dc1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 14:57:55 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] drivers/tty/8250: translate serial8250_do_startup/shutdown
 control flow to Rust, wire live (Tier C, linux-rs TU 38, awto-au/linux-rs#25)

Translates serial8250_do_startup()/serial8250_do_shutdown() control
flow (branching, ordering, error handling) to
drivers/tty/serial/8250/8250_startup_rs.rs, wired into the live
.startup/.shutdown uart_ops via a new CONFIG_RUST_8250_STARTUP Kconfig
option (deliberately separate from CONFIG_RUST, which already gates
the landed Tier A/B translations in this same driver).

struct uart_port/uart_8250_port stay opaque (*mut c_void) on the Rust
side -- neither struct has bindgen bindings in this tree, and both are
large/deeply nested (embedded spinlock, op-table function pointers,
DMA/RS485 sub-structs). Every field access and subsystem call the C
originals perform is exposed as a narrow extern "C" shim function in
8250_port.c (serial8250_startup_rs_*), a one-for-one mechanical mirror
of each line of the C bodies -- the Rust side carries only the control
flow. upf_t flag-bit tests stay in C (not a stable UAPI type, evaluated
in C so width/encoding can't drift between languages).

NO KUNIT COVERAGE, BY DESIGN: both functions call the real IRQ
subsystem (request_irq/synchronize_irq/free_irq via
ops->setup_irq()/release_irq()) and take the real port spinlock. Per
docs/8250-tier-c-blocker-2026-07-18.md, a KUnit fake can stand in for
data (Tier B's register buffer) but not for "the interrupt subsystem
accepted this registration" -- faking that would mean reimplementing
genuine IRQ-core semantics inside the test. Dan explicitly accepted
this as a scoped exception (2026-07-18, awto-au/linux-rs#25), gated
instead on a byte-for-byte side-by-side boot-transcript comparison
against the unmodified C path across 3 repeat boots per side: clean
from "KTAP version 1" (start of KUnit output) through end of
transcript across all 6 logs, zero deviation. See
docs/8250-tier-c-startup-shutdown-2026-07-18.md (linux-rs repo) for
the full comparison record.

dev.py check: 17/17 KUnit suites, ORACLE PASS, INIT REACHED, SPDX
PROVENANCE PASS (37/37 translated files).
